title: Tigard High School Technology Team
subtitle: FTC 3965 - Lead Programmer
description: Robotics set me on the path to becoming a software engineer. I learned so much about programming, engineering, and teamwork. I was the lead programmer for the team for 4 years and I loved every minute of it. I am so grateful for the experience and guidance from my mentors and teachers. I look forward to mentoring a team someday in the future.

title: International Collegiate Programming Contest
description: I love competative programming! It is such a fun way to enhance my skills in a collaborative and competative environment. I have competed in the ICPC twice and I am looking forward to competing again next year.

title: OSU's ACM Chapter
description: The ACM has been a great way to network with other students, develop my skills, and find new opportunities. I have been a member of the ACM since my first year at OSU and I have always loved the supportive environment it promotes. I look forward to attending the club and helping other students find their passion for computer science.

title: App Development Club
description: The App Dev club at OSU has become another great way to network with other students.
